---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../../components/Footer.astro';

const title = 'Privacy Policy';
const description = 'How THREADLINE processes personal data, user content, files, technical data, and requests sent to AI agents.';
const updatedAt = 'June 24, 2026';

const sections = [
  {
    title: '1. Who processes the data',
    body: [
      'The operator of the THREADLINE service is Marina Rinatovna Kalmykova.',
      'Additional operator details, including address and registration information, will be added after they are finalized.',
      'For privacy and personal data questions, contact legal@threadline.tigerapps.pro.'
    ]
  },
  {
    title: '2. Information we process',
    body: [
      'Account data: email address, name or display name, protected password data or third-party sign-in data, plan, subscription status, registration date, and profile settings.',
      'User content: boards, cards, text, files in different formats, images, documents, links, references, relationships between objects, versions, reminders, and other materials that a user creates or uploads to THREADLINE.',
      'Technical data: IP address, device type, browser, operating system, interface language, approximate country or region, sign-in time, error logs, security events, and performance data.',
      'Usage data: actions inside the service, opened areas, operations with boards and files, integration settings, material update history, and service object identifiers.'
    ]
  },
  {
    title: '3. Files, originals, and user content',
    body: [
      'THREADLINE is built for storing and connecting user materials. The user decides which files, ideas, images, documents, links, and notes to upload to the service.',
      'We use user content only to provide THREADLINE functionality: rendering boards, storing files, creating relationships, updating materials, preparing previews, enabling downloads, restoring access, and supporting the user.',
      'We do not claim ownership of user content. Rights to uploaded materials remain with the user or the rights holder on whose behalf the user acts.'
    ]
  },
  {
    title: '4. AI agents and external integrations',
    body: [
      'If a user connects AI agents or external services, THREADLINE may transmit selected user data to those services only to perform the action requested by the user.',
      'The user is responsible for choosing the external AI provider, configuring the integration, and selecting the data sent through such integrations.',
      'We do not use user content to train our own or third-party AI models without the user’s separate explicit consent.'
    ]
  },
  {
    title: '5. Payment data',
    body: [
      'If paid THREADLINE plans are enabled, payments may be processed by external payment providers. Full bank card details, CVV/CVC, and payment authentication data are entered on the payment provider side and are not stored by THREADLINE.',
      'THREADLINE may receive limited payment information: plan, amount, currency, payment status, operation date, transaction identifier, and payer email if provided by the payment provider.',
      'Information about the specific payment provider and payment recipient details will be added after the payment setup is finalized.'
    ]
  },
  {
    title: '6. Cookies and analytics',
    body: [
      'We may use cookies, local storage, and similar technologies for authentication, session storage, account protection, remembering settings, error diagnostics, and product analytics.',
      'Analytics are used to understand load, interface quality, errors, and feature usage. If separate marketing or advertising pixels are connected, information about them will be added to this policy.'
    ]
  },
  {
    title: '7. Why we process information',
    body: [
      'To create accounts, authenticate users, and provide access to THREADLINE.',
      'To store and display boards, cards, files, relationships, versions, reminders, and other user materials.',
      'To maintain service security, prevent abuse, investigate errors, and protect accounts.',
      'To respond to support requests, send important service notices, and comply with legal obligations.',
      'To improve product performance, interface quality, reliability, and stability.'
    ]
  },
  {
    title: '8. Sharing information with third parties',
    body: [
      'We may share data only to the extent necessary for THREADLINE to operate: with hosting providers, object storage providers, email and infrastructure services, payment providers, analytics tools, security services, and AI providers selected by the user.',
      'Contractors and providers receive access only to the data required to perform a specific technical or contractual function.',
      'We may also disclose data if required by law, court order, request from an authorized public authority, or to protect the rights, safety, and legitimate interests of THREADLINE and its users.'
    ]
  },
  {
    title: '9. Retention and security',
    body: [
      'We keep data for as long as needed to operate the account, perform obligations, maintain security, resolve disputes, and comply with applicable legal requirements.',
      'After account deletion, some data may remain for a limited time in backups, security logs, payment records, and legally significant records where necessary.',
      'We apply technical and organizational safeguards: access controls, protected password storage, encrypted connections, backups, security logs, and error monitoring. However, no method of transmission or storage is absolutely secure.'
    ]
  },
  {
    title: '10. User rights',
    body: [
      'A user may request access to their data, correction, deletion, restriction of processing, export of data, or account termination.',
      'Some data cannot be deleted immediately where retention is required for security, payment accounting, tax, anti-fraud, or other mandatory purposes.',
      'To make a personal data request, contact legal@threadline.tigerapps.pro from the email address linked to the account or provide information that allows us to verify the account relationship.'
    ]
  },
  {
    title: '11. Children',
    body: [
      'THREADLINE is not intended for independent use by children below the age at which they can consent to personal data processing under applicable law.',
      'If you believe a child has provided personal data to us without the required consent, contact legal@threadline.tigerapps.pro.'
    ]
  },
  {
    title: '12. Changes to this policy',
    body: [
      'We may update this policy as THREADLINE evolves, new features or providers are connected, payment flows are introduced, or legal requirements change.',
      'The current version is published on this page. If changes materially affect user rights, we will try to notify users in a noticeable way.'
    ]
  },
  {
    title: '13. Contact information',
    body: [
      'Operator: Marina Rinatovna Kalmykova.',
      'Privacy email: legal@threadline.tigerapps.pro.',
      'Support email: support@threadline.tigerapps.pro.'
    ]
  }
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  canonical="https://landing-bvn34s5k5p.82.21.153.180.sslip.io/en/legal/privacy"
  lang="en"
  ogLocale="en_US"
>
  <Header locale="en" />
  <main class="pt-[128px] pb-24 px-6">
    <article class="legal-doc max-w-[820px] mx-auto">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-between gap-3 mb-8">
        <a href="/" class="text-[12px] hover:text-white transition-colors" style="color: hsl(255,8%,55%);">← Home</a>
        <a href="/legal/privacy" class="language-link">Русская версия</a>
      </div>

      <p class="eyebrow">THREADLINE Legal</p>
      <h1>{title}</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        This policy explains what information THREADLINE processes, why the service needs it, and how users can manage their data.
      </p>
      <p class="updated">Last updated: {updatedAt}</p>

      <div class="notice">
        This document is prepared for the current public version of THREADLINE. Details that have not yet been confirmed are not invented and will be added later.
      </div>

      <div class="sections">
        {sections.map((section) => (
          <section>
            <h2>{section.title}</h2>
            {section.body.map((paragraph) => <p>{paragraph}</p>)}
          </section>
        ))}
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
  <Footer locale="en" />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-doc {
    color: hsl(260, 20%, 92%);
  }

  .language-link {
    height: 34px;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
    border-radius: 9px;
    padding: 0 12px;
    font-size: 12px;
    color: hsl(255,8%,72%);
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
    transition: color 160ms ease, border-color 160ms ease, background 160ms ease;
  }

  .language-link:hover {
    color: white;
    border-color: rgba(66,223,193,0.34);
    background: rgba(66,223,193,0.08);
  }

  .eyebrow {
    margin: 0 0 14px;
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--mint);
  }

  h1 {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: 'Space Grotesk', 'Inter', system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(36px, 6vw, 64px);
    line-height: 0.98;
    letter-spacing: 0;
  }

  .lead {
    margin: 22px 0 0;
    max-width: 720px;
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.72;
    color: hsl(255,8%,70%);
  }

  .updated {
    margin: 18px 0 0;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: hsl(255,8%,52%);
  }

  .notice {
    margin: 34px 0 0;
    border: 1px solid rgba(66,223,193,0.18);
    border-radius: 14px;
    padding: 18px 20px;
    background: rgba(66,223,193,0.055);
    color: hsl(255,8%,76%);
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .sections {
    margin-top: 42px;
    display: grid;
    gap: 34px;
  }

  section {
    padding-top: 2px;
  }

  h2 {
    margin: 0 0 14px;
    font-family: 'Space Grotesk', 'Inter', system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-size: 22px;
    line-height: 1.25;
    letter-spacing: 0;
  }

  section p {
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    color: hsl(255,8%,68%);
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.72;
  }

  section p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .legal-doc {
      max-width: 100%;
    }

    .notice {
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 16px;
    }

    h2 {
      font-size: 20px;
    }
  }
</style>
